      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it might be \"theoretical\" for the general public, but think about the incentive. if they could use existing hardware to gauge consumer sentiment or even predict when someone might be more prone to impulse buying due to stress, the data would be worth billions. wouldn't a company like that skip the \"theoretical\" stage and just pilot these things on certain users or groups to see if it works? it feels way too specific to be a coincidence every time it happens to me.",
